---
import { href } from "../lib/href";
import facts from "../generated/facts.json";

const REPO = "https://github.com/crypticpy/build-a-claude-harness";
const sha = (facts as { shortSha?: string }).shortSha ?? "";
const settingsUrl = (facts as { provenance?: { settings?: string } }).provenance?.settings ?? REPO;

const outcomes = [
  "Name the points in a session where you can run your own code and change what the AI does.",
  "Explain how one router runs all of them, so adding a behavior doesn't mean rewiring.",
  "Describe how the AI keeps its memory through long tasks, after the conversation is trimmed.",
  "Explain how an approval step can hold back actions that can't be undone.",
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A visual guide to how an AI coding harness works. An AI model can't touch the files on your computer on its own; a harness gives it that ability, and decides how complex and how long a task it can handle. Built on Claude Code."
    />
    <link rel="icon" href={href("favicon.svg")} />
    <title>Harness Atlas: how an AI coding harness works</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="topbar">
      <span class="topbar-brand">Harness Atlas</span>
      <span class="topbar-tag">A visual guide · built on Claude Code</span>
    </header>

    <main id="main">
      <section class="hero">
        <h1>How an AI coding harness works</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          An AI model can't open, read, or change the files on your computer. On its own, it only
          produces text. A harness is the software around the model that connects it to your project and
          lets it act: read and edit files, run commands, and check its own work.
        </p>
        <p class="lede">
          What goes into a harness does more than give the model file access. It sets how complex a task
          the model can take on, and how long it can keep working before it needs you. Claude Code is a
          harness. This site explains how it works, one part at a time, and how you can extend it. You
          don't need to write code to follow it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="start" aria-labelledby="start-h">
        <h2 id="start-h">How the AI gets work done</h2>
        <p class="start-lede">
          Claude Code works in a loop: it reads your project, makes a plan, changes a file, checks the
          result, and repeats until the task is done. It doesn't finish in one step. The first
          walkthrough follows this loop through a single request, one step at a time.
        </p>
        <div class="start-cards">
          <a class="card card--primary" href={href("agent-loop")}>
            <span class="card-tag">Start here</span>
            <span class="card-title">The agent loop</span>
            <span class="card-sub">
              Follow one request through the loop that turns it into finished code, one step at a time.
            </span>
            <span class="card-go">Open the walkthrough →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="card" href={href("how-it-works")}>
            <span class="card-tag">Next</span>
            <span class="card-title">Inside a real harness</span>
            <span class="card-sub">
              The same loop wired to a real settings file: the points where you can change what the AI
              does, the router behind them, and how it keeps memory between sessions.
            </span>
            <span class="card-go">See how it's wired →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="outcomes" aria-labelledby="outcomes-h">
        <h2 id="outcomes-h">By the end, you can</h2>
        <ul class="outcomes-list">
          {
            outcomes.map((o) => (
              <li class="outcome">
                <span class="outcome-mark" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
                <span>{o}</span>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="phases" aria-labelledby="phases-h">
        <h2 id="phases-h">The two phases</h2>
        <p class="phases-lede">
          Lesson 1 covers the parts of Claude Code and what each one does. Lesson 2 shows how to combine
          them into a more capable setup.
        </p>
        <nav class="phase-nav" aria-label="Lessons">
          <a class="phase-card" href={href("phase-1")}>
            <span class="phase-tag">Lesson 1</span>
            <span class="phase-title">How Claude Code works</span>
            <span class="phase-sub">
              The parts, one at a time: tool calls, planning, memory, hooks, commands, skills,
              subagents, and MCP. It ends with a stock setup building a small program.
            </span>
            <span class="phase-go">Start Lesson 1 →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="phase-card" href={href("phase-2")}>
            <span class="phase-tag">Lesson 2</span>
            <span class="phase-title">Customizing Claude Code</span>
            <span class="phase-sub">
              How to combine those parts into a setup that handles longer, more complex tasks. Our
              harness is one example, not the only way.
            </span>
            <span class="phase-go">Start Lesson 2 →</span>
          </a>
        </nav>
      </section>

      <section class="closing">
        {
          sha && (
            <p class="prov">
              Every claim links to the exact line of the real harness it came from, pinned to commit{" "}
              <a href={settingsUrl} rel="noopener"><code>{sha}</code></a>. Nothing here is invented for
              the lesson.
            </p>
          )
        }
        <p class="closing-links">
          <a href={href("agent-loop")}>Start with the agent loop →</a>
          <a href={REPO} rel="noopener">Source on GitHub</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <style is:global>
      :root {
        --paper: #fbfaf6;
        --paper-2: #ffffff;
        --ink: #221f1a;
        --ink-soft: #5c554b;
        --ink-faint: #968d7d;
        --hair: #e6e0d4;
        --hair-strong: #d6cdbb;
        --context: #2f6bd8;
        --action: #c9740a;
        --verified: #1f9a63;
        --risk: #d6453f;
        --serif: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", Palatino, "Book Antiqua", Georgia, ui-serif,
          serif;
        --sans: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial,
          sans-serif;
        --mono: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }
      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }
      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: var(--sans);
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
      }

      .topbar {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 18px clamp(20px, 5vw, 56px);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hair);
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--paper) 92%, transparent);
        z-index: 20;
      }
      .topbar-brand {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 17px;
        color: var(--ink);
      }
      .topbar-tag {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-faint);
      }

      main {
        max-width: 1180px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 clamp(20px, 5vw, 56px);
      }

      /* ---- hero ---- */
      .hero {
        padding: clamp(56px, 11vh, 128px) 0 clamp(32px, 6vh, 64px);
        max-width: min(74ch, 100%);
      }
      .hero h1 {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: clamp(34px, 6vw, 60px);
        line-height: 1.07;
        letter-spacing: -0.015em;
        margin: 0 0 28px;
      }
      .lede {
        font-size: clamp(18px, 2.2vw, 22px);
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
        max-width: 62ch;
        margin: 0 0 20px;
      }
      .lede:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      /* ---- section heads ---- */
      .start,
      .outcomes,
      .phases {
        padding-block: clamp(40px, 8vh, 88px) 0;
      }
      .start h2,
      .outcomes h2,
      .phases h2 {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: clamp(26px, 3.6vw, 40px);
        line-height: 1.1;
        letter-spacing: -0.012em;
        margin: 0 0 16px;
      }
      .start-lede,
      .phases-lede {
        font-size: clamp(17px, 2vw, 20px);
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
        max-width: 62ch;
        margin: 0 0 32px;
      }

      /* ---- start cards ---- */
      .start-cards {
        display: grid;
        gap: clamp(16px, 2.5vw, 24px);
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      }
      .card {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 8px;
        padding: clamp(22px, 3vw, 32px);
        background: var(--paper-2);
        border: 1px solid var(--hair);
        border-radius: 16px;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: var(--ink);
        box-shadow:
          0 1px 2px rgba(40, 38, 32, 0.04),
          0 16px 36px -28px rgba(40, 38, 32, 0.22);
        transition:
          border-color 0.16s ease,
          transform 0.12s ease,
          box-shadow 0.16s ease;
      }
      .card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-2px);
        border-color: var(--hair-strong);
        box-shadow:
          0 1px 2px rgba(40, 38, 32, 0.05),
          0 24px 48px -28px rgba(40, 38, 32, 0.28);
      }
      .card--primary {
        border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--action) 45%, var(--hair));
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--action) 5%, var(--paper-2));
      }
      .card--primary:hover {
        border-color: var(--action);
      }
      .card-tag {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--action);
      }
      .card-title {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(21px, 2.6vw, 27px);
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: 1.15;
      }
      .card-sub {
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
        margin-top: 2px;
      }
      .card-go {
        margin-top: auto;
        padding-top: 14px;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--context);
      }

      /* ---- outcomes ---- */
      .outcomes-list {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        display: grid;
        gap: 16px 40px;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        max-width: 90ch;
      }
      .outcome {
        display: flex;
        gap: 14px;
        align-items: baseline;
        font-size: clamp(16px, 1.8vw, 18px);
        line-height: 1.5;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
      }
      .outcome-mark {
        color: var(--action);
        font-weight: 700;
        flex: none;
      }

      /* ---- phases ---- */
      .phase-nav {
        display: grid;
        gap: clamp(16px, 2.5vw, 24px);
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      }
      .phase-card {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 6px;
        padding: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px);
        background: var(--paper-2);
        border: 1px solid var(--hair);
        border-radius: 16px;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: var(--ink);
        transition:
          border-color 0.16s ease,
          transform 0.12s ease;
      }
      .phase-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-2px);
        border-color: var(--hair-strong);
      }
      .phase-tag {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-faint);
      }
      .phase-title {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 26px);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .phase-sub {
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
        margin-top: 2px;
      }
      .phase-go {
        margin-top: 10px;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--context);
      }

      /* ---- closing ---- */
      .closing {
        padding: clamp(48px, 9vh, 104px) 0 clamp(72px, 14vh, 140px);
        max-width: 72ch;
      }
      .prov {
        font-size: 15px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--ink-faint);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--hair);
        padding-top: 22px;
        margin: 0 0 24px;
      }
      .prov code {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--action) 9%, var(--paper-2));
        padding: 1px 7px;
        border-radius: 6px;
        color: var(--action);
      }
      .prov a {
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      .closing-links {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 14px 28px;
        margin: 0;
      }
      .closing-links a {
        color: var(--context);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 16px;
      }
      .closing-links a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      @media (max-width: 760px) {
        .start-cards,
        .phase-nav,
        .outcomes-list {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }

      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        html {
          scroll-behavior: auto;
        }
        .card,
        .phase-card {
          transition: none;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
